290
00:15:35,180 --> 00:15:36,380
I have a Wilkes Browning machine gun

291
00:15:36,380 --> 00:15:38,060
in the car.

292
00:15:38,580 --> 00:15:40,340
Also, I have a professional gunner.

293
00:15:40,660 --> 00:15:42,180
It’s harder than fighting in a war

294
00:15:42,380 --> 00:15:44,100
if I meet bandits.

295
00:15:46,780 --> 00:15:48,300
Look at the blood on my clothes.

296
00:15:49,540 --> 00:15:51,900
It’s from a bandit who was killed by me this morning.

297
00:15:52,220 --> 00:15:53,260
Mr. Cheng.

298
00:15:53,500 --> 00:15:55,580
You really contributed a lot.

299
00:15:56,340 --> 00:15:57,820
But we have our rule.

300
00:15:58,460 --> 00:16:01,380
We share everything with each other.

301
00:16:01,660 --> 00:16:03,060
But you take that road as your own,

302
00:16:03,220 --> 00:16:04,660
which is against the rule.

303
00:16:04,660 --> 00:16:06,020
Yes.

304
00:16:06,020 --> 00:16:07,540
Please make it clear.

305
00:16:07,740 --> 00:16:09,860
Don’t ask me to obey your rule.

306
00:16:10,980 --> 00:16:11,940
When did I join

307
00:16:11,940 --> 00:16:13,740
your Peking Chamber of Commerce?

308
00:16:15,020 --> 00:16:16,580
What’s more,

309
00:16:16,660 --> 00:16:17,900
everyone goes their own way.

310
00:16:18,220 --> 00:16:20,740
No one stops you if you go through that road.

311
00:16:21,860 --> 00:16:22,740
Mr. Cheng.

312
00:16:24,260 --> 00:16:25,820
Mind your words.

313
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:27,900
We’ll pay you

314
00:16:28,100 --> 00:16:29,180
for using your road.

315
00:16:29,180 --> 00:16:30,100
Can you rent it to us?

316
00:16:30,100 --> 00:16:30,820
Yes.

317
00:16:30,820 --> 00:16:31,220
Yes.

318
00:16:31,220 --> 00:16:32,340
We’ll pay you.

319
00:16:34,420 --> 00:16:37,420
I risked my life

320
00:16:38,340 --> 00:16:42,460
to fight against the bandits for it.

321
00:16:43,140 --> 00:16:44,340
It's not for rent.

322
00:16:44,980 --> 00:16:46,300
But my friends can use it without paying me.

323
00:16:47,740 --> 00:16:48,820
As I said before,

324
00:16:49,100 --> 00:16:50,700
it’s easy to be my friends.

325
00:16:51,500 --> 00:16:53,340
Donate the half of your profits

326
00:16:53,860 --> 00:16:54,820
for the anti-Japanese war

327
00:16:55,140 --> 00:16:56,820
in the northeast of China.

328
00:16:56,980 --> 00:16:57,700
The half?

329
00:16:58,420 --> 00:16:59,420
That’s too much.

330
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:01,180
Cheng Fengtai.

331
00:17:01,620 --> 00:17:02,420
Your brother-in-law

332
00:17:02,420 --> 00:17:04,339
is a commander with troops.

333
00:17:04,619 --> 00:17:05,940
So you are overweening now?

334
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:07,020
Yes.

335
00:17:07,140 --> 00:17:08,099
Bandits on the road?

336
00:17:08,099 --> 00:17:09,859
I think you are just a bandit!

337
00:17:09,859 --> 00:17:10,500
Yes!

338
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:11,619
You are a bandit!

339
00:17:11,619 --> 00:17:12,460
Freeze!

340
00:17:12,619 --> 00:17:13,140
Freeze!

341
00:17:23,460 --> 00:17:24,579
(Zheng Yuanmu)

342
00:17:24,579 --> 00:17:26,220
What’s going on?
(Zheng Yuanmu)

343
00:17:26,220 --> 00:17:27,099
(Zheng Yuanmu)

344
00:17:28,820 --> 00:17:29,700
Mr. Cheng.

345
00:17:29,980 --> 00:17:31,900
I’m just late for a while.

346
00:17:32,060 --> 00:17:34,660
Welcome me with a troop?

347
00:17:37,700 --> 00:17:38,420
Chairman Zheng.

348
00:17:38,540 --> 00:17:40,700
We just want to appreciatively

349
00:17:40,700 --> 00:17:41,820
borrow a way from Mr. Cheng.

350
00:17:41,820 --> 00:17:43,220
I heard it.

351
00:17:43,740 --> 00:17:45,740
How muddled you are.

352
00:17:46,220 --> 00:17:47,940
You've been doing business for years,

353
00:17:47,940 --> 00:17:49,140
but why haven’t you known

354
00:17:49,540 --> 00:17:51,260
how to communicate with others?

355
00:17:51,860 --> 00:17:53,860
It’s our great honor that Mr. Cheng

356
00:17:53,860 --> 00:17:55,700
came here.

357
00:17:55,860 --> 00:17:57,140
Look at you.

358
00:17:57,140 --> 00:18:00,340
You picked faults with him in various ways.

359
00:18:00,700 --> 00:18:01,540
What?

360
00:18:02,220 --> 00:18:03,660
Does he owe you?

361
00:18:05,060 --> 00:18:05,940
All of you, sit down.

362
00:18:11,820 --> 00:18:12,780
Mr. Cheng.

363
00:18:14,100 --> 00:18:15,820
It’s my fault.

364
00:18:15,980 --> 00:18:17,500
I didn’t lead them well.

365
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:18,420
Could you

366
00:18:18,420 --> 00:18:19,580
forgive them

367
00:18:20,140 --> 00:18:22,420
for me?

368
00:18:23,060 --> 00:18:24,820
They are businessmen.

369
00:18:24,820 --> 00:18:28,340
Your weapons will

370
00:18:28,540 --> 00:18:30,980
scare them to death.

371
00:18:38,500 --> 00:18:39,900
Your words work

372
00:18:40,460 --> 00:18:41,980
for me.

373
00:18:43,220 --> 00:18:44,140
But

374
00:18:44,900 --> 00:18:46,900
I don’t have appetite

375
00:18:47,060 --> 00:18:48,940
on your feast.

376
00:18:49,700 --> 00:18:51,060
So I won’t

377
00:18:51,060 --> 00:18:52,700
force you to stay.

378
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:54,060
Well,

379
00:18:54,460 --> 00:18:57,540
I’ll hire an opera troupe

380
00:18:58,060 --> 00:19:00,580
to perform at Huibin Theatre to apologize to you.

381
00:19:01,340 --> 00:19:04,300
Please accept my apology and come.

382
00:19:07,700 --> 00:19:08,980
Of course

383
00:19:09,460 --> 00:19:10,860
I’ll accept your invitation.

384
00:19:11,420 --> 00:19:12,500
Thanks.

385
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:15,540
Take care.

386
00:19:26,180 --> 00:19:27,140
Thank you for your hard work.

387
00:19:27,340 --> 00:19:28,340
Go back to have a rest.

388
00:19:28,420 --> 00:19:29,380
Thanks, Mr. Cheng.

389
00:19:34,660 --> 00:19:36,380
Seems that you won.

390
00:19:37,620 --> 00:19:39,140
Arguing with some losers

391
00:19:39,140 --> 00:19:40,300
needs some tricks.

392
00:19:41,460 --> 00:19:42,660
I’ve put your clothes

393
00:19:42,660 --> 00:19:43,620
in the car.

394
00:19:44,140 --> 00:19:45,380
Will we go home?

395
00:19:49,820 --> 00:19:51,220
Let’s go to Little Mansion first

396
00:19:51,420 --> 00:19:52,220
to catch Fan Lian.

397
00:20:31,740 --> 00:20:32,380
Mr. Cheng.

398
00:20:32,620 --> 00:20:33,540
I urged him.

399
00:20:33,780 --> 00:20:36,020
Mr. Fan asked us to wait for a while.

400
00:20:36,980 --> 00:20:38,900
It’s been a long time.

401
00:20:41,260 --> 00:20:41,740
Go.

402
00:20:42,460 --> 00:20:44,740
Break the windows with stones.

403
00:20:46,500 --> 00:20:47,540
Go.

404
00:20:57,980 --> 00:20:58,860
Oh my god.

405
00:20:59,300 --> 00:21:00,180
What are you doing?

406
00:21:02,780 --> 00:21:03,780
What are you doing?

407
00:21:04,220 --> 00:21:05,060
What did you say?

408
00:21:08,540 --> 00:21:12,540
This is my house. It’s none of your business.

409
00:21:19,060 --> 00:21:19,780
Continue.

410
00:21:21,820 --> 00:21:22,420
OK.

411
00:21:25,660 --> 00:21:26,700
Mr. Fan.

412
00:21:31,500 --> 00:21:31,740
Mr. Cheng?

413
00:21:31,740 --> 00:21:32,300
(Fan Lian)
Mr. Cheng?

414
00:21:32,300 --> 00:21:33,340
(Fan Lian)

415
00:21:33,340 --> 00:21:34,220
I’m coming.
(Fan Lian)

416
00:21:34,220 --> 00:21:34,980
Wait me.
(Fan Lian)

417
00:21:34,980 --> 00:21:35,620
Just me a minute.

418
00:21:40,020 --> 00:21:40,740
Mr. Cheng.

419
00:21:41,260 --> 00:21:42,220
You are here?

420
00:21:50,380 --> 00:21:52,900
(Zeng Aiyu)

421
00:21:53,580 --> 00:21:54,940
Don’t you go upstairs?

422
00:22:03,460 --> 00:22:03,940
Mr. Fan.

423
00:22:18,340 --> 00:22:19,540
I asked you to go to the chamber for me,

424
00:22:19,540 --> 00:22:20,700
but why didn’t you listen?

425
00:22:21,260 --> 00:22:22,700
Does it work?

426
00:22:22,860 --> 00:22:25,020
My words are not deterrent to those old guys.

427
00:22:25,140 --> 00:22:26,860
They are always against me.

428
00:22:26,860 --> 00:22:28,420
Look how coward you are.

429
00:22:29,420 --> 00:22:30,940
- Mrs. Cheng.
- We are back.

430
00:22:31,580 --> 00:22:33,100
I’m back!

431
00:22:33,180 --> 00:22:34,100
Welcome back.

432
00:22:37,540 --> 00:22:38,940
I miss you so much.

433
00:22:39,820 --> 00:22:41,380
Why did you go back late?

434
00:22:41,380 --> 00:22:42,260
Yes.

435
00:22:42,260 --> 00:22:43,740
What things delayed you?

436
00:22:43,820 --> 00:22:45,820
Mrs. Cheng was on tenterhooks.

437
00:22:48,340 --> 00:22:51,580
Fan Lian and I went to the chamber of commerce.

438
00:22:54,180 --> 00:22:55,060
Tell them

439
00:22:55,180 --> 00:22:57,220
to cook lobsters and vegetarian hams

440
00:22:57,220 --> 00:22:58,180
for Mr. Cheng.

441
00:22:58,300 --> 00:22:58,820
Yes.

442
00:22:58,940 --> 00:22:59,780
Wait.

443
00:23:00,100 --> 00:23:00,740
Xiang’er.

444
00:23:01,020 --> 00:23:02,740
How about my pork with pickles?

445
00:23:03,020 --> 00:23:04,300
I’m starving.

446
00:23:04,380 --> 00:23:05,340
I only want this.

447
00:23:05,820 --> 00:23:06,460
Go.

448
00:23:06,460 --> 00:23:07,340
What?

449
00:23:07,380 --> 00:23:08,700
Tell Chacha’er to come to have lunch.

450
00:23:08,700 --> 00:23:09,380
OK.

451
00:23:10,060 --> 00:23:10,620
Come.

452
00:23:11,100 --> 00:23:12,300
Let’s have lunch.

453
00:23:12,980 --> 00:23:14,620
Thank you

454
00:23:14,620 --> 00:23:17,140
- for preparing this for me.
- Give me a set of tableware.

455
00:23:20,100 --> 00:23:22,380
It’s really different after my brother-in-law comes back.

456
00:23:25,580 --> 00:23:27,260
How thickskinned you are.

457
00:23:27,940 --> 00:23:28,740
What?

458
00:23:28,740 --> 00:23:30,740
Today, two men came here

459
00:23:31,260 --> 00:23:32,620
to find you.

460
00:23:33,420 --> 00:23:35,380
You must not know why they came.

461
00:23:36,540 --> 00:23:37,980
They came to ask for payment of your debts.

462
00:23:41,340 --> 00:23:43,180
They asked me

463
00:23:43,820 --> 00:23:45,140
whether Mr. Fan

464
00:23:45,140 --> 00:23:46,220
has money.

465
00:23:46,220 --> 00:23:46,940
If he has money,

466
00:23:46,940 --> 00:23:48,540
how come he hasn’t paid his debts?

467
00:23:48,860 --> 00:23:49,780
If he doesn’t,

468
00:23:50,700 --> 00:23:53,180
how could he reward the performers

469
00:23:53,180 --> 00:23:54,900
in Shuiyun Theater with five gold ingots?

470
00:23:56,500 --> 00:23:57,340
Come on, Xiang’er.

471
00:23:57,860 --> 00:23:59,220
I am wronged.

472
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:01,780
I gave them for my friends.

473
00:24:02,340 --> 00:24:03,940
They need a chance to show off.

474
00:24:06,460 --> 00:24:07,500
Am I right, Mr. Cheng?

475
00:24:07,620 --> 00:24:08,460
My lady,

476
00:24:08,740 --> 00:24:09,820
have a shrimp.

477
00:24:17,580 --> 00:24:18,340
Meixin.

478
00:24:19,340 --> 00:24:21,100
I can’t help you on this.

479
00:24:21,500 --> 00:24:22,900
I’ll help you

480
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:24,420
if you rewarded other performers.

481
00:24:24,420 --> 00:24:26,620
But Shuiyun Theatre is run by Shang Xirui.

482
00:24:27,140 --> 00:24:29,660
He’s the opera performer who I dislike most.

483
00:24:30,100 --> 00:24:31,260
Can you be generous?

484
00:24:31,260 --> 00:24:32,260
No, I can’t.

485
00:24:32,380 --> 00:24:34,660
Shang Xirui?

486
00:24:35,220 --> 00:24:36,940
My disloyal brother.

487
00:24:37,180 --> 00:24:38,580
You should have slapped him.

488
00:24:38,740 --> 00:24:40,180
How come you rewarded him?

489
00:24:42,220 --> 00:24:43,020
You rarely went out.

490
00:24:43,020 --> 00:24:44,740
How did you

491
00:24:45,220 --> 00:24:47,540
become the enemy of an opera performer?

492
00:24:47,540 --> 00:24:49,020
How could I become a performer’s enemy?

493
00:24:49,700 --> 00:24:52,300
That’s because of my cousin and his wife.

494
00:24:53,980 --> 00:24:55,140
What’s

495
00:24:55,140 --> 00:24:56,420
the story?

496
00:24:57,380 --> 00:24:58,060
Fengtai!

497
00:24:59,060 --> 00:25:00,620
Chacha’er comes. Stop it.

498
00:25:00,860 --> 00:25:01,860
Fengtai! You are back!

499
00:25:02,820 --> 00:25:04,020
Why didn’t you come back earlier?

500
00:25:04,020 --> 00:25:05,460
I miss you so much.

501
00:25:05,660 --> 00:25:06,260
Good girl.

502
00:25:06,260 --> 00:25:06,700
Come.

503
00:25:06,700 --> 00:25:08,060
Sit beside me.

504
00:25:08,500 --> 00:25:09,100
Hurry.

505
00:25:09,340 --> 00:25:09,980
Mrs. Cheng.

506
00:25:10,340 --> 00:25:10,900
Good girl.

507
00:25:10,900 --> 00:25:11,660
Eat.

508
00:25:13,540 --> 00:25:14,180
Sit here.

509
00:25:19,820 --> 00:25:21,380
Just ignore our sister?

510
00:25:22,420 --> 00:25:23,420
Be polite.

511
00:25:26,180 --> 00:25:27,620
This girl can

512
00:25:28,020 --> 00:25:29,620
only see you.

513
00:25:30,660 --> 00:25:31,460
(Chacha’er)

514
00:25:31,460 --> 00:25:33,260
The shrimp peeled by you tastes so good.
(Chacha’er)

515
00:25:33,260 --> 00:25:34,300
(Chacha’er)

516
00:25:34,340 --> 00:25:35,020
One more.

517
00:25:43,380 --> 00:25:44,340
How’s your leg?

518
00:25:44,540 --> 00:25:45,620
Do I need to call a doctor here?

519
00:25:46,300 --> 00:25:46,900
It’s all right.

520
00:25:47,540 --> 00:25:48,980
I fell down from a horse several days ago.

521
00:25:48,980 --> 00:25:49,900
It’s almost healed.

522
00:25:53,780 --> 00:25:55,300
You didn’t tell me the whole story at the lunch.

523
00:25:55,900 --> 00:25:57,220
How did your cousin and his wife

524
00:25:57,860 --> 00:25:59,300
have a story with the opera performer

525
00:25:59,300 --> 00:26:00,460
surnamed Shang?

526
00:26:01,460 --> 00:26:02,500
It’s a tragedy.

527
00:26:03,420 --> 00:26:04,660
When they were in Pingyang,

528
00:26:04,660 --> 00:26:05,820
Shang Xirui

529
00:26:05,820 --> 00:26:08,780
learned opera with my cousin-in-law, Jiang Mengping.

530
00:26:09,580 --> 00:26:11,460
He was in love with Jiang Mengping ever since being a child.

531
00:26:11,780 --> 00:26:12,780
But Jiang Mengping

532
00:26:12,780 --> 00:26:14,380
didn’t return his affection.

533
00:26:14,860 --> 00:26:16,220
He didn’t drop the idea.

534
00:26:16,900 --> 00:26:18,020
Then, Jiang Mengping

535
00:26:18,020 --> 00:26:20,140
fell in love with my cousin, Chang Zhixin.

536
00:26:20,220 --> 00:26:22,020
When they prepared for their wedding,

537
00:26:22,900 --> 00:26:24,940
Shang Xirui made a scene

538
00:26:24,940 --> 00:26:26,140
to stop her marrying my cousin.

539
00:26:26,660 --> 00:26:28,700
He even suppressed her

540
00:26:29,060 --> 00:26:30,980
with forbidding her to perform in other opera troupes.

541
00:26:31,700 --> 00:26:32,860
What’s worse,

542
00:26:32,860 --> 00:26:34,340
he also created an opera based on their story

543
00:26:34,620 --> 00:26:36,300
and performed it every day.

544
00:26:36,420 --> 00:26:37,820
Now, everyone knows it.

545
00:26:39,020 --> 00:26:40,500
Which opera?

546
00:26:40,820 --> 00:26:42,060
How can I know?

547
00:26:42,900 --> 00:26:44,820
Everyone has right to marry the one she loves.

548
00:26:45,380 --> 00:26:47,340
It’s he who should be blamed

549
00:26:47,580 --> 00:26:48,740
due to his love to his senior fellow.

550
00:26:48,940 --> 00:26:50,460
It’s shameless of him

551
00:26:50,900 --> 00:26:52,540
to spread this story.

552
00:26:54,900 --> 00:26:55,940
He’s like

553
00:26:56,700 --> 00:26:59,500
the celebrities of Broadway.

554
00:26:59,700 --> 00:27:01,740
When they feel wronged, they’ll shout it out,

555
00:27:02,100 --> 00:27:02,780
make it published in newspapers,

556
00:27:03,140 --> 00:27:03,900
have a press,

557
00:27:04,060 --> 00:27:04,820
and write an autobiography.

558
00:27:05,140 --> 00:27:06,060
This will help them to be known by more people.

559
00:27:06,220 --> 00:27:07,180
And then they’ll hype it more.

560
00:27:07,580 --> 00:27:09,100
What Broadway?

561
00:27:10,060 --> 00:27:12,580
The women who show their legs on your posters?

562
00:27:12,940 --> 00:27:14,300
Indecent.

563
00:27:15,260 --> 00:27:16,620
You are wrong.

564
00:27:16,700 --> 00:27:17,940
This is for the performance.

565
00:27:17,940 --> 00:27:18,940
They are professional actresses.

566
00:27:18,940 --> 00:27:21,180
Those who flirt with the audiences

567
00:27:21,500 --> 00:27:22,540
and open their legs in pants?

568
00:27:22,740 --> 00:27:23,820
Indecent.

569
00:27:25,420 --> 00:27:26,220
OK. OK.

570
00:27:26,820 --> 00:27:29,780
What you said is Bible.

571
00:27:30,260 --> 00:27:30,980
You...

572
00:27:31,740 --> 00:27:33,980
Are you thinking about women on your posters

573
00:27:34,300 --> 00:27:35,620
or those actresses?

574
00:27:35,980 --> 00:27:37,580
Which one am I thinking about?

575
00:27:39,700 --> 00:27:41,740
I’d rather think about your cousin-in-law.

576
00:27:42,860 --> 00:27:44,860
Two men fought for her.

577
00:27:45,340 --> 00:27:47,140
She must be a beauty.

578
00:27:47,580 --> 00:27:48,500
Yes.

579
00:27:48,500 --> 00:27:49,620
She’s a beauty.

